how is this one i welcome constructive criticism lol dark curse never dead not living no beat in silent hearts no breath in still lungs thoughts racing in still minds they roam the earth in the hours of darkness feel their gaze know their hunger they lust for the warmth of your body to taste your blood and for a brief moment to know life passionate kisses sweet embrace dance of flesh within flesh carnal delights magnified climax reached with thundering pulse and with final kisses sipping crimson draining life and stealing your soul know the seductive bite close your eyes and welcome oblivion slipping away only to be pulled back her blood on your lips it is done open your eyes now take her hand and from death be alive yet not living never dead silent heart still lungs racing thoughts in still mind your soul is lost heaven s gate barred shunned by hell s flames know what it means to be damned know that you are forsaken some purists will have a hard time with my poetry i prefer verse libre and spoken word over standard styles although i will use the standards on occasion my poetry is not usually about happy cheery stuff i've been working the night shift for all of my adult life and my poetry is either about the beauty of the night or uses darker subjects flavors i loved it it was fantastick make another one i give you a star i also liked how it gripped my attention right away The Amber Spyglass Kain (Legacy of Kain) Sin City Hell Blood (computer game) Love Sant Thakar Singh Time Out of Mind Shakespeare's sonnets Soul Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Milton H. Erickson Death Original sin Ten Commandments YuYu Hakusho Naruto jutsu Dean Koontz Characters of Naruto InuYasha media and release information Queen (band) Resurrection of Jesus Vampire Bhagavad Gita Jon Secada Hamlet Italian literature Miss Saigon Angel Sanctuary Heart The Death Gate Cycle Characters of The Sandman Waking the Dragons Prince Edmund (Blackadder) Beatrice Portinari The Cure Fallen angel